page.title: 03ECOLOGY
page.content: Foxes and deer are often seen in the area.Wild rabbits abound together squirels,moles and farm cats.Domestic dogs move about freely.Bird life is prolific:there are owls,magpies,sparrows,chaffinches,buzz ards,crows,various tits,song thrushes,starlings and swifts which visit each year and nest in the eaves of local houses.All land is undulating with various degrees of steepness.There are winding narrow tarmac lanes and high tree lined hedges of hawthorne and bramble.Primroses abound in the spring and honysuckle and travellers joyclamber along the hedgerows.
